                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/8076: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-13T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 13, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 13—2:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>143. My 135, June 6, 5 p.m. The Embassy has been reliably informed that Monsieur
                    Badouin, a well-known French banker, has arrived unofficially in Rome in an
                    effort to convince the Italians that the French Government has for all practical
                    purposes closed all Pyrenees frontiers and also to ascertain whether it would
                    not be possible to reopen the Franco-Italian negotiations. No publicity
                    whatsoever is being given to this confidential mission of Monsieur Badouin who
                    is also desirous of ascertaining the Italian preference regarding the person to
                    be named as the French Ambassador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
